{"title":"Baby Evacuation Aprons","link":"https://kottke.org/24/11/baby-evacuation-aprons","date":1731597911000,"content":"\n        <p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/baby-evac-apron-01.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/baby-evac-apron-01.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/baby-evac-apron-01.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1300\" height=\"1589\" alt=\"a woman wearing a baby evacuation apron with three fake babies in it going down some fire escape stairs\" /></p>\n\n<p>Today I learned about <a href=\"https://www.baby-mover.com/en/evacuation-apron/\">evacuation aprons</a>, which places like maternity wards use to rescue infants and toddlers in case of emergency or fire. Or as this labor &amp; delivery nurse on Threads <a href=\"https://www.threads.net/@im_a_mia/post/DCUdj8ox_6y\">put it</a>:</p>\n\n<blockquote><p>â€¦the goal is to grab your vest and just stuff as many babies as humanly possible in its giant kangaroo pockets before running out the door.</p></blockquote>\n\n<p>This particular company sells a few different models, like <a href=\"https://www.baby-mover.com/en/newborn-baby-mover/\">this apron for newborns</a> and <a href=\"https://www.baby-mover.com/en/baby-mover/\">this one for larger infants and toddlers</a> that can carry a total weight of 60 lbs. All the aprons are fire-resistant.</p>\n\n<p>There is also something called <a href=\"https://www.medsled.com/product/med-sled-infant-6-insert-set/\">the Med Sled</a>, which can carry up to 6 infants at a time.</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/baby-evac-apron-02.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/baby-evac-apron-02.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/baby-evac-apron-02.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1118\" height=\"975\" alt=\"a medical carrier with spaces for carrying six babies at once\" /></p>\n\n        \n\n         <p><strong>Tags:</strong> <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/fashion\">fashion</a> Â· <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/healthcare\">healthcare</a></p>\n\n         <p>ðŸ’¬ <a href=\"https://kottke.org/24/11/baby-evacuation-aprons\">Join the discussion on kottke.org</a> â†’</p>\n\n    ","author":"Jason Kottke","siteTitle":"Kottke","siteHash":"89a883271b4598f9b33ebe87be70d38557bcd266e68aee521a8f93622e0ab723","entryHash":"bb8218898d3deef2cbc7508ea55bcbb0fc337b5d3cf4214d9715e284b2fe2a55","category":"Sites"}